A building's roof collapsed in Durban leaving multiple people injured. DURBAN - eThekwini Municipality shut down the Dr Pixley Ka Seme Street building on Friday in Durban after nine people were injured when the roof collapsed. READ: eThekwini Municipality owed over R11bn The people, including a three-year-old child, were injured when a roof collapsed in the Durban CBD on Thursday. READ: Nine injured in Durban building roof collapse The eThekwini Human Settlements and Infrastructure Committee Chairperson, Thanduxolo Sabelo, says all the injured have since been discharged from hospital.